<html xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_4.xsd" xmlns:p="tapestry:parameter">
	<div class="container">
		<h3>Tapestry Delegate and Block component</h3>
		<p>When a template becomes complex or cluttered in a way that makes its structure or sequence of elements difficult, consider using Delegate and Block.</p>
		<div class="fbox">
			<p>
				<t:delegate to="block:blockA"/>
		        <t:delegate to="block:blockB"/>
		        <t:delegate to="block:blockC" project="flywind"/>
		        Nothing...
			</p>
			<p>
				<t:block id="blockA">
			        <div style="padding: 10px; background-color: green; color:#fff;">
			            This is block A.
			        </div>
			    </t:block>
			</p>
			<p>
				<t:block id="blockC">
			        <div style="padding: 10px; background-color: red; color:#fff;">
			            This is block C.
			        </div>
			    </t:block>
			</p>
			<p>
				<t:block id="blockB">
			        <div style="padding: 10px; background-color: blue; color:#fff;">
			            This is block B.
			        </div>
			    </t:block>
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</html>